list.abstract: over，英文单词，可作介词、副词、形容词、动词和名词，在句中可用作状语、主语、宾语和表语，翻译为结束，穿过，越过，多于等。
标题曲「OVER」是一首旨在鼓励人们振作起精神"一起向前迈进"的应援歌曲。此外，普通盘还收录了初回限定盘中未收录的「爱ing -アイシテル-」。

yingyinNormal.en: Hey, guys! That doesn't count. Do over! Do over!
yingyinNormal.zh: 好啊，伙计们！那个不算，重来！重来！

yingyinNormal.en: It's over! The game's over! Leon's dead! You hear me?
yingyinNormal.zh: 都结束了！游戏结束了！里昂死了！听懂了没？

yingyinNormal.en: She's reading the same book over and over. She's depressed.
yingyinNormal.zh: 她会把同一本书读了又读。她有些抑郁。
莱丽，你就克服你的恐惧吧。

yingyinNormal.en: You. Me. All of us. It's over.
Put them over there in the sink.

yingyinNormal.zh: 我会下令让朝中众臣都支持你。
这样浪费时间就太没诚意了，山姆。
阿奇漫画都在那边呢。好滴。

direction_info.description:
数据源自2012-2023年12年间全国考研试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2012-2023年全国考研英语一和考研英语二共24套考研试卷，包括阅读、完型填空、翻译、写作等所有题型。

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>
精选全国考研考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2012-2023年12年间全国考研英语一和考研英语二试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

word_family.mean: prep. 直接向上延伸的；在…的上方；在…的上空；通过；过；高于；在…之上；超过；关于；在…方面

examination_example.sentence: Successive governments have presided <highlight>over</highlight> selling green spaces, squeezing money from local authorities and declining attention on sport in education.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 历届政府都卖过绿地，从地方政府压榨资金并减少对体育教育的关注。

examination_example.sentence: Protests have erupted <highlight>over</highlight> construction of the Thirty Meter Telescope (TMT), a giant observatory that promises to revolutionize humanity's view of the cosmos.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 关于三十米望远镜的建造引发了抗议，这是一个有望彻底改变人类对宇宙看法的巨大天文台。

examination_example.sentence: This new focus on personal fulfillment can help keep employees motivated amid increasingly loud debates <highlight>over</highlight> work-life balance.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在关于工作与生活平衡的争论日益激烈的情况下，这种对个人成就感的新关注有助于保持员工的积极性。

sense_info_list.en: during something, or while doing something

examination_example.sentence: The researchers compared that data to reported changes in fluid intelligence <highlight>over</highlight> a six-year period.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 研究人员将这一数据与六年期间所报告的流体智力变化进行了比较。

examination_example.sentence: However, <highlight>over</highlight> the past 12 months, those commuters have also experienced some of the worst rail strikes in years.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 然而，在过去的12个月里，这些通勤者也经历了几年来最严重的铁路罢工。

examination_example.sentence: 60,000 extra new homes could be built <highlight>over</highlight> the next five years if the cap were lifted, increasing GDP by 0.6%.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 如果借贷限额被取消，在未来5年能够修建60000套新房，使国内生产总值提高0.6%。

sense_info_list.en: more than a particular amount or level

examination_example.sentence: At the start of this century, about one-third of crop workers were <highlight>over</highlight> the age of 35.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 本世纪初，大约三分之一的农作物工人年龄超过35岁。

examination_example.sentence: A counteraction against the <highlight>over</highlight>-tweeting trend.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 对过度发推趋势的抵制。

examination_example.sentence: And <highlight>over</highlight> 30 is considered obese.
examination_example.sentence_trans: （体重指数）超过30以上被认为是肥胖。

examination_example.sentence: As many took on the duty of trying to integrate reasoning and scientific philosophies into the world, the Renaissance was <highlight>over</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 当许多人承担起将推理和科学哲学融入世界的责任时，文艺复兴已经结束。

examination_example.sentence: Average is officially <highlight>over</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 平均水平正式结束了。

examination_example.sentence: The great recession may be <highlight>over</highlight>, but this era of high joblessness is probably beginning.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 大衰退可能已经结束，但这个高失业率的时代可能正在开始。

sense_info_list.zh: 在...上方; 高于; 优先于

examination_example.sentence: Labour triumphs <highlight>over</highlight> status.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 工党战胜了地位。

examination_example.sentence: Qualified multilingual youngsters from other countries are proving to have a competitive advantage <highlight>over</highlight> their British counterparts in global companies and organisations.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 事实证明，在跨国公司和组织中，来自其他国家符合条件且掌握多门语言的年轻人比英国同龄人有竞争优势。

examination_example.sentence: The Conservatives' planning reform explicitly gives rural development priority <highlight>over</highlight> conservation, even authorising "off-plan" building where local people might object.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 保守党的规划改革明确将农村发展置于保护之上，甚至授权当地居民可能反对的“规划外”建设。

sense_info_list.zh: (表示动作的结果)...过来; 过

examination_example.sentence: Take <highlight>over</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 接手。

examination_example.sentence: Turn <highlight>over</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 翻过来。

examination_example.sentence: Five ways to win <highlight>over</highlight> everyone in the office.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 赢得办公室里每个人的支持的五种方法。

examination_example.sentence: To win <highlight>over</highlight> these young workers, manufacturers have to clear another major hurdle: parents, who lived through the worst US economic downturn.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 要说服这些年轻的工人，制造商必须清除另一个障碍：家长。他们经历了美国最严重的一次经济下行。

examination_example.sentence: People responded best to comments that shifted from negative to positive, possibly because it suggested they had won somebody <highlight>over</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 人们对从负面转为正面的评论反应最好，可能是因为这表明他们赢得了某人的好感。

examination_example.sentence: The Royal Free hospital trust handed <highlight>over</highlight> to DeepMind the records of 1.6 million patients in 2015.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 皇家免费医院在2015年向深度思维公司移交160万名病人的记录。

sense_info_list.en: in or on all or most parts of sth

examination_example.sentence: On a recent sunny day, 13,000 chickens roam <highlight>over</highlight> Larry Brown's 40 windswept acres in Shiner, Texas.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在最近一个阳光明媚的日子里，13,000只鸡在拉里·布朗位于德克萨斯州希纳的40英亩微风吹拂的农场上漫步。

examination_example.sentence: Fascinates AI scientists all <highlight>over</highlight> the world.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 让全世界的AI科学家着迷。

sense_info_list.en: from a higher to a lower position

examination_example.sentence: It makes it hard to disengage, and leads to a lot of bleed-<highlight>over</highlight> into the family routine.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这让人很难不沉浸其中，也会导致家庭日常受到重大影响。

examination_example.sentence: You wish that you could turn back the clock and start <highlight>over</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 你希望时光倒流，重新开始。

(row over)一路领先; 轻易取胜

word_usage.usage: above和over均可表示位置高于…或在…上， 表示从某物的一边移至另一边只能用over；over亦可表示覆盖着。表示“多于”时，above与最低限度或某固定点关联，如：2000 feet above sea level海拔2 000英尺；over与数目、数量、年龄、金钱和时间连，如：He’s over 50.他已年过半百。

<highlight>考纲释义</highlight>
精选实考、考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2016-2023年51套试卷，包括阅读、听力、翻译等所有题型。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2016-2023年8年间全六级试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

sense_info_list.en: more than a particular amount or level

examination_example.sentence: He was granted <highlight>over</highlight> 200 patents and continued to pioneer rocket technology until his death in 1945.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他获得了200多项专利，并继续开拓火箭技术，直到1945年去世。

examination_example.sentence: Under a minute could seem rushed, while <highlight>over</highlight> two minutes, will start to feel more like a speech.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 不到一分钟可能会显得匆忙，而超过两分钟，会开始感觉更像是一场演讲。

examination_example.sentence: All 67 participants were <highlight>over</highlight> 60 years of age, and both groups lost about the same amount of weight.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 67名参与者全部都在60岁以上，两组人的体重减轻量大致相同。

examination_example.sentence: After the MSc diploma is earned, there would be many more stamps of lifelong learning <highlight>over</highlight> the years.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 获得理学硕士文凭后，这些年将会有更多终身学习的类型。

examination_example.sentence: <highlight>Over</highlight> the years the power dynamic has changed and is no longer defined by one being the giver and another, the taker.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 多年来，权力的动态发生了变化，不再由一个是给予者，另一个是接受者来定义。

examination_example.sentence: <highlight>Over</highlight> the years, Tim Joseph 's partners have helped many dairy farmers to switch to grass-fed.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 多年来，Tim Joseph 的合作伙伴帮助许多奶农改用草饲。

examination_example.sentence: In fact, the polarised debate <highlight>over</highlight> public health interventions should have been abandoned long ago.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 事实上，关于公共卫生干预措施的两极分化辩论早就应该被摒弃了。

examination_example.sentence: What does the speaker say about being <highlight>over</highlight> collaborative?
examination_example.sentence_trans: 关于过度合作，说话者说了什么？

examination_example.sentence: A) The confusion <highlight>over</highlight> food expiration labels.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 食品过期标签上的混乱。

examination_example.sentence: D) Colleges exercise foil control <highlight>over</highlight> their own financial affairs.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 大学对自己的财务行使控制权。

examination_example.sentence: It resulted in an oil surplus all <highlight>over</highlight> the world.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这导致了全世界的石油过剩。

examination_example.sentence: Ultimately, social media has increased our ability to connect with various types of people all <highlight>over</highlight> the globe.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 最终，社交媒体增强了我们与全球各类人联系的能力。

examination_example.sentence: I use the term "low-tier" cautiously, because GSU is a well-regarded research institution that attracts high quality professors and faculty from all <highlight>over</highlight> the country.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我谨慎地使用“低层次”这个词，因为GSU是一个备受尊敬的研究机构，吸引了来自全国各地的高质量教授和教员。

examination_example.sentence: The board game Go (围棋) took <highlight>over</highlight> from chess as a new test for human thinking in 2016.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 棋盘游戏围棋在2016年接替象棋成为人类思维的新测试。

examination_example.sentence: He took <highlight>over</highlight> the sales department of Reader's Digest.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他接管了《读者文摘》的销售部。

examination_example.sentence: It seems that consumers are growing more uneasy about handing <highlight>over</highlight> the massive amounts of consumer data needed to provide the personalized, customized solutions.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 消费者似乎越来越不愿意交出大量的消费者数据，而这些数据又是提供个性化定制解决方案所需要的。

sense_info_list.en: across; from one side or place to another

examination_example.sentence: The most toxic part of decision making is going <highlight>over</highlight> the same options time and time again.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 决策过程中危害最大的部分就是一次又一次地重复同样的选择。

examination_example.sentence: Three-quarters of the world's flamingos fly <highlight>over</highlight> from other salt lakes in the Rift Valley.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 世界上四分之三的火烈鸟是从东非大裂谷的其他盐湖飞过来的。

examination_example.sentence: Until then they've been giving everything they have and at that moment they know it's <highlight>over</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在那之前，他们一直在付出他们所拥有的一切，在那一刻，他们知道一切都结束了。

examination_example.sentence: According to Moen, flexibility gives employees better control <highlight>over</highlight> their work and time.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 莫恩说，灵活性让员工更好地控制自己的工作和时间。

examination_example.sentence: It won <highlight>over</highlight> Coke executives in Atlanta and would go on to receive its own trademark.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 它赢得了可口可乐在亚特兰大的高管们的支持，并将获得自己的商标。

word_usage.usage: over一般表示“在…的正/垂直上方，above一般强调物体间的上下关系，不一定存在垂直关系。在不需要特别强调垂直上方的语境里，两个词可以互换。
over and over和over and over again都表示“屡次地”，后者为英国人常用。
stay over night表示“过夜，住宿”，这个短语中的over night可连写为overnight。

word_usage.usage: over and over和over and over again都表示“屡次地”，后者为英国人常用。
